description: For sale in our Denver showroom is a fine example of a classic American muscle car, a 1970 Dodge Dart Swinger. This two owner, Tor Red Mopar has a black bumble bee stripe and black vinyl top that really brings you back to classic styling of the late 60s and early 70s. The Dodge Dart was first introduced in 1960 as the "smallest full sized" Dodge. In 70, the "Swinger" name was applied to all the Dart two-door hardtops except in the high-line custom series. A number of other changes were made to the Dart line to avoid internal competition with Dodge's new Challenger. The performance model in the Dart line for 1970 was the Swinger 340 2-door hardtop. The 1970 Swinger 340 came with functional hood scoops with 340 emblems. Standard equipment included front disc brakes, heavy duty "Rallye" suspension, a 3.23:1 rear axle ratio (now a 3.55:1), fiberglass-belted bias-ply tires mounted to 14" Ãƒ? 5Ã‚Â½" steel wheels, and a bumble bee stripe. Originally a 318 V8, now under the dual snorkel hood sits a powerful 360 CID V8 backed by a 727 TorqueFlite automatic transmission. The 360 exhales from TTI headers into customer exhaust which is sure to turn heads. Options include: AM/FM/CD radio, power front disc brakes, power steering, seat belts, raised white letter radial tires, and rally wheels. If you are looking for a great classic car to enjoy without the timely and costly headache of a restoration, look no further. To view the car in greater detail, including an HD video and HD pictures, please visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com or our Denver showroom. Call 303-872-4722 for more information.
title: 1970 Dodge Dart

description: This Dart is the poster child  for a southern, rust-free car with all original sheet metal! Solid and original floors and trunk floor – it’s tough to come by one this original and clean! This one oozes class with its beautiful black ragtop and crisp white interior. Formerly a 6 cylinder, a modified 360 cubic inch V8 now rests under the hood topped with a 4 barrel Edelbrock carburetor taking this Dart from ho-hum to eat my GT dust!  A smooth Torque Flite 3-speed automatic transmission and power steering makes for effortless driving and the dual exhaust lets them all know this Mopar is more than a pretty face. You’ll notice the elegant, luxury touches throughout on this nicely presented Mopar. The sheetmetal is straight, original, and in excellent shape with tight fitting doors. The chrome is nicely presented from nose to tail with all trim and badges in place. The dash is classic ‘60’s style with a 120 mph readout speedometer and stock AM radio and original heat/defrost controls. Full spare tire with jack rests in the trunk. The staggered tires - 225/65/15 front and 255/60/15 rear performance radials lend a subtle, yet aggressive stance to this sophisticated classic. This is a very nice and complete convertible showing off all its details and square-jawed angles and ultra clean interior that makes you pay attention!

description: Set up like a vintage drag racer this is a rust free car that's been beautifully restored. Has a monster engine, 4 speed and 3.91 posi. South Carolina car, the floors are original and rock solid. The body and paint is one of the better ones we have in our showroom. The car is arrow straight when you look down the sides. There's not a bubble or a blister anywhere I could find. It has been block sanded and polished to a mirror finish from the roof all the way down to the rockers. Door jambs are glossy. The paint is further enhanced by the exceptionally nice chrome and trim. Stainless is polished, bumpers and taillights are chromed, grill and trunk trim are not abused. Has steel hood with functional super stock style hood scoop. Vintage reproduction Radir wheels in front, wide steel rims in back.  Interior has been restored. Seats have been reupholstered, door panels, carpet and headliner have been replaced. Dash area looks very nice. It's a radio delete. Has seat belt front and back. Aftermarket tachometer and gauges.  Trunk is clean, has a new mat. Motor compartment is detailed up very nicely.

The motor is a 440 that's been balanced, bored and stroked to a 512. Dyno tuned at 695 hp and 645 lbs of torque. All the best parts used- forged crank and rods, Keith Black pistons, ported heads, ARP bolts etc. Has Mopar high rise intake with Demon 830 carb. Rebuilt Hemi trans, new Hurst shifter, rebuilt 3.91 posi rear, new disc brake conversion. Has headers and a fat exhaust. This car shakes the building.
The previous owner was asking $44,000. We considered asking $34,998 but priced it at $29,998. Someone will get a steal!

description: For sale in our St. Louis showroom is a Plum Crazy Purple 1972 Dodge Dart Swinger. The odometer reads 83,046, the actual mileage is unknown, and there are approximately 300 miles on the car since the build was complete. Options for this 1972 Dodge Dart Swinger include: Air Conditioning, AM/FM with CD Player, Power Brakes, Power Steering, Seat Belts, Vinyl Interior, Radial Tires, and Aluminum/Alloy Wheels. Powering the Plum Crazy Mopar is a 340 CID V8 engine that has been internally balanced and features chrome valve covers and air cleaner, a Street Dominator aluminum intake, and a Summit Racing carburetor. Headman Headers flow to the stainless exhaust and provide a great sound. A 727 Torqueflight automatic transmission with a 3000 stall converter transfers the power to the 8 3/4 open rear end with 3.23 gears. The Plum Crazy Purple paint features a base coat/clear coat application, and was sprayed in late 2016. The black vinyl upholstery is in very good condition, very plush and soft, and is free from any rips or tears. The dash features a subtle wood grain treatment, which blends very well with the black dash and seats. This Dart Swinger definitely stands out in a crowd, from its aggressive stance and dual snorkel hood scoop to its Plum Crazy paint, you can't miss this bad boy. Eat up corners also with disc front brakes, a front sway bar & 15" M&H radials on all four corners.

Upgrades and maintenance recently done: Front suspension lower control arm & strut bushings all replaced with OE spec rubber for quiet operation & added welding to K-member near the steering gear & lower control arm tube.  Speedo rebuilt for improved accuracy and quietness, & new MOPAR battery installed.
Track tested @ US 131 Drag strip 4-23-2016 ET 13.5 @ 103 mph on pump gas and no pinion snubber.  Driven to the track and back from Holland, MI 70 miles round trip.
Odometer reads 89,600 miles.  Title reads "actual miles unknown".
l. Engine:  340 4bbl Engine block cast 01-15-1973 #2780930. bored.030" over hypereutectic pistons, melling MC1735 cam.  Forged crank .020" under.

Cast Iron Intake cast#3462838 modified to accept larger primaries of the 440 AVS
340 X cylinder heads cast #2581894 date coded 08-22-1969
2015 updated version Rev-N-Nator ignition & matched coil with Chrysler distributor.  Features built in soft touch rev limiter and LED tach on box.
Exhaust TTI 1 5/8” nickel chrome plated step headers & 2.5” X-pipe without chrome tips, Dynomax mufflers.

ll. Drive Train: A833 date code 1-22-1969 4 speed Pistol grip lever with Hurst comp plus positive stop mechanism with dash reverse indicator.  10.95” McLeod diaphragm clutch with a new bell crank & throw-out bearings.
Drive shaft small u-joint custom length & balanced with drive shaft loop.  Welded in sub frame connectors.
8 ¾” rear axle #742 case 3.91: 1 ratio with clutch style sure grip, Moser axels, and new bearings & seals
’73 K member /front suspension with disc brakes, sway bar & donut style Schumacher engine mounts.
Wheels 15” X 7” “police”, dodge division dog dish caps, & set of 4 new M&H  drag radial tires size 26/8.5 15” front & 235/60 15“ rear.
New 22” radiator with AMS oil coolant and dominator coolant boost, fan shroud and MOPAR 5 blade viscous fan package.
lll. Interior:  Black bucket seats with belts for 5 passengers.  No shoulder harnesses due to missing male retractors.
Grant Steering wheel “Tuff Wheel” look alike.

description: Offered here is a highly original and affordable classic Dodge Dart. 1966 marked the final year of the third generation model, with production ending all together in 1976, before the recent reemergence in the past few years. This example is not perfect; however, it is a quality classic driver and comes with some incredible first owner documentation. Per the original bill of sale, Karen Bond of Detroit, MI purchased this car new on July 21,1966 through Colonial Dodge, Inc. of East Detroit. It also comes with the original sets of keys with dealer tag, factory build sheet, original owners manual, maintenance booklet, and the original title.     The car is finished in a D code Medium Blue paint, which looks silver in different lighting, over a L1B code Blue interior. This 170 model is powered by the original 273ci/180hp V8 mated to a 3-speed automatic transmission with a 2.72 rear end. Other noteworthy features include front disc brakes, aluminum radiator, Edelbrock head with 4bbl carburetor, and 5-spoke sport wheels. This car starts, runs, and drives well. An affordable classic Dart with some awesome curb appeal. See over 100 photos and video on our website. Call or e-mail if interested, or to make a reasonable offer. Thank you for looking.
